 The Managing Director of the Bank of Industry, Mr. Olukayode Pitan, has urged State and Federal Governments to establish more universities of technology to drive development. Pitan gave the advice during the ancillary meeting at the 25th Nigerian Economic Summit in Abuja on Tuesday. The 2019 summit has as its theme: “Nigeria 2050 Shifting Gears”. He said the country must identify the kind of education that would guarantee accelerated development. Continue reading BOI MD calls for more technology varsities to drive dev’t at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard